# 1848

label rel_1848_danish_war:
    scene bg prussia office

    show schleswig sad at left
    show schleswig sad with vpunch

    "Schleswig bursts into your office, knocking over an inkwell."

    sw "Helpppppp!"

    show prussia normal at right

    p "I swear by the Iron Cross, if you ruined my Krupp artillery requisition forms..."
    
    show holstein frustrated at center
    
    h "It's Denmark! That bi- she's trying to annex Schleswig!" 
    h "She's marching troops right up to the border!"

    sw "I-I thought things were going better with her... she said she'd leave me forever and cancel the personal union!"

    h "You have to do something! You're the biggest military power in the Confederation!"
    
    show prussia smug

    p "That Denmark needs to learn her lesson! I've had enough of her bullying you two!"

    p "If Copenhagen wants to test the temper of my steel, I am more than happy to oblige. Consider the vanguard mobilized."
    
    "Schleswig and Holstein look at you with absolute adoration as you casually sign the mobilization orders."
    
    scene bg schleswig battlefield with fade
    
    "April 1848. The fields of Jutland."
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "General Wrangel! Push the infantry past the Danewerk! I want the Danish defenses crushed before sundown!"
    p "Let's remind her who holds the true power in the North!"
    
    "Your armies smash through the Danish lines with terrifying efficiency."
    "The Danish forces are routed at the Battle of Schleswig. Your troops march triumphantly deep into Jutland, occupying the territory."
    
    show holstein joyful at left
    show schleswig joyful at right
    
    h "You did it! You actually pushed them back!"
    sw "We're safe! Oh, Prussia, you are magnificent on the battlefield!"
    
    show prussia joyful at center
    
    p "Hmph. It was barely a warm-up."
    p "Let's march on Copenhagen and finish this!"

    show holstein at offscreenleft
    
    "Before you can issue the order, a courier rides into the command tent, his horse foaming at the mouth."
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    p "What is it!? Can't you see I'm busy manifesting my destiny!?!??"
    
    "The courier hands you two sealed letters. One bears the crest of the British Royal Navy. The other, the two-headed eagle of the Russian Tsar."
    
    show prussia serious
    
    "You break the seals and read them."
    "The air in the tent suddenly grows freezing cold."
    
    p "...The Tsar is massing troops on my eastern border. He demands I withdraw immediately."
    p "And the British are threatening to blockade my entire coastline if the Baltic balance of power is upset."
    
    show schleswig intense
    
    sw "Wait... what does that mean?"
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    p "Bah!!!! I can't fight a two-front war against the Great Powers!"
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "Wrangel! Halt the advance! Send an envoy to Malmö. Tell the Danes we will sign an armistice."
    
    h "But... the Frankfurt Parliament! They ordered you to secure our total freedom!"
    
    p "The Parliament has no army. I do. And I am not sacrificing Berlin to the Russians for a couple of farms in Jutland."
    p "The war is over. I saved you from annexation, but I am not conquering Denmark today."
    
    scene bg negotiation room

    uk "Right. Well. If everyone has had a chance to review the terms... perhaps we can move forward with the signing?"
    
    show denmark smug at right
    
    dk "I am perfectly happy with the terms. A complete withdrawal of Prussian troops from Schleswig and Holstein. As it should be."
    
    show prussia frustrated at left
    
    p "Wipe that smirk off your face, Denmark. We both know my artillery shattered your lines at the Danewerk. You didn't win this war."
    
    dk "And yet, here you are, signing a surrender. Funny how that works, isn't it?"
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "I swear, if we were in that field right now, I would—"
    
    "A heavy, gloved hand slams onto the table, rattling the inkwells."
    
    show russia intense at center
    
    ru "Enough."
    ru "You will not threaten the Danish crown, little eagle. The Tsar has decreed that the Baltic balance of power remains unchanged. Or do I need to march two hundred thousand men across the Vistula to remind you?"
    
    show britain intense at right
    hide denmark
    
    uk "Quite right. The Royal Navy is currently holding its position just outside your ports, Prussia."

    uk "We simply cannot have a unified German state controlling both sides of the Danish straits. It's bad for trade. Sign the paper, be a good girl, and we'll sail the fleet home."
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    "You grind your teeth so hard your jaw aches. Your blood is boiling, screaming at you to draw your sword."

    "However, your navy consists of a few glorified fishing boats. Your industry is not enough. A two-front war against the British blockade and the Russian army means total annihilation."
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "Fine. But let the record show I am doing this for the stability of Europe, not because I recognize Danish authority over the duchies."
    
    show britain smug
    
    uk "Let the record show whatever makes you feel better, dear. Just sign the document."
    
    "You snatch the quill, aggressively signing your name to the Armistice of Malmö."
    
    show prussia normal
    
    p "There. Are you happy? My troops will pull out by the end of the week."
    
    show russia normal
    
    ru "A wise decision. See that they do."
    
    "Russia and Britain collect the documents, acting like you are nothing more than a misbehaving child they just scolded."
    
    jump turn_start

label rel_1848_bavaria_scandal:
    scene beerhall
    show bavaria drunk at right

    b "A-and then... *hic*... she demanded a title! A title!"

    show prussia neutral at left

    p "Just breathe, Bavaria. Here, drink some water."

    show bavaria sad

    b "She wasn't even Spanish, Prussia! She was just an Irish actress named Eliza! And my King... my King!... threw away the entire crown for her!"
    
    b "The university was rioting! The streets were on fire! Over a fake flamenco dancer!"

    show prussia frustrated

    p "Yeah, that's... definitely one way to lose a throne..."

    p "I brought you some schnapps, by the way. Let's just slide this over here..."

    "You push a heavy glass across the table. Bavaria immediately downs it and buries her face in the table."

    show bavaria drunk

    b "Austria is going to make fun of me forever. The whole Confederation is laughing at me..."

    show prussia normal

    p "Hey... Half the continent is on fire right now..."
    
    show prussia joyful

    p "If your biggest problem is a messy royal scandal, you're actually doing great."

    show bavaria embarrassed

    b "You're... you're not going to make fun of me?"

    show prussia smug

    p "Oh, I'm definitely gonna make fun of you later, just not today."

    p "Austria is too busy yelling at people in the Frankfurt Parliament to care about you right now anyway."

    "Bavaria sniffles, reaching out to grab your sleeve."

    show bavaria drunk

    b "You're actually a pretty good friend when you aren't trying to militarize my borderssss..."

    p "Don't push it. Now drink your water before you pass out on my boots."

    "You spend the rest of the evening acting as emotional support, earning her trust while Austria is completely distracted."

    jump turn_start

