label rel_1848_mecklenburg_date:
    scene bg field
    
    "You take a brief carriage ride out of the city to the Baltic coast, seeking refuge from the endless screaming and burning barricades."
    
    "You find Mecklenburg standing in the middle of a massive, sun-drenched wheat field, happily chewing on a piece of straw."
    
    show mecklenburg joyful at right

    mv "Thank you for visiting, Prussia. I'm sorry it's not very exciting here."
    
    show prussia joyful at left
    
    p "Mecklenburg, 'exciting' is currently trying to burn down my palace. This is perfect."

    show prussia smug

    p "Do you hear that? Listen closely."

    "Mecklenburg nervously looks around the empty field."

    show mecklenburg embarrassed

    mv "I... I just hear the wind. And maybe a cow."

    p "Exactly. No gunfire. No parliamentarians demanding constitutions. Just absolute, glorious silence."

    show mecklenburg normal 

    p "I have to say, I am incredibly impressed with your discipline. While the rest of the Confederation is throwing a massive, collective temper tantrum, you haven't had a single proper riot."

    show mecklenburg embarrassed

    mv "Oh, well... it's not really discipline. We just don't have enough paved roads for a proper mob to march on."
    
    mv "And the peasants are too spread out with the harvest to read any of those liberal pamphlets..." 
    
    mv "It's mostly just dirt and feudalism up here... we're a bit behind the times..."

    show prussia serious

    p "Don't sell yourself short!"

    show prussia normal

    p "While everyone else is busy writing poetry and burning effigies, you're keeping us all fed!"
    
    p "It's highly efficient."
    p "I happen to find efficiency very attractive."

    show mecklenburg embarrassed with vpunch 

    "Mecklenburg's face turns almost as red as a revolutionary flag. She desperately tries to hide behind a bundle of harvested wheat."

    mv "T-thank you..." 

    mv "I'll, um... I'll make sure to keep the grain yields high for you..."

    "You spend a surprisingly peaceful afternoon walking through the fields, enjoying the company of the one state in Germany that isn't on fire."
    
    jump turn_start